Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Chop the @potatoes{450%grams} lengthways into 1cm slices, then chop into 1cm wide chips (no need to peel).

Pop the chips onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with oil, then sprinkle over the @mixed herbs{1%sachet} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer. 

> Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, bake on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, put the @cornflour{20%grams} and @peri peri seasoning{1%sachet} into a large #bowl{} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Mix to combine. Add the @British chicken thighs{3} to the bowl of cornflour and toss to coat well.

> Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Put a large #frying pan{} on high heat and add enough oil to completely coat the bottom of the pan.

> You want the oil to be hot so the chicken fries properly - heat for 2-3 mins before you add the chicken.

Once the oil is hot, carefully lay the chicken into the pan, reduce the heat to medium-high and fry until golden-brown and cooked through, ~{12-14%minutes} total. Turn every 2-3 mins and adjust the heat as necessary. Discard any cornflour left in the bowl. Once cooked, remove from the heat and place the chicken onto #kitchen paper{}.

> The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

While the chicken cooks, boil a half-full #kettle{}. Trim the @green beans{80%grams}, then cut into thirds. Zest and halve the @lime{1}.

Pour the boiled water into a medium #saucepan{} with @salt{1/2%tsp} on high heat. Bring back to the boil, then add the beans and cook until just tender, ~{4-5%minutes}. Add the @peas{120%grams} to water and cook ~{1%minute} more.

Drain in a #colander{}, then return the cooked veg to the saucepan. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Stir through the lime zest and half the @butter{20%grams}. Cover with a #lid{} to keep warm and set aside.

While everything cooks, put your (now empty) frying pan back on medium-low heat (no need to clean). Add the @honey{15%grams}, lime juice and the remaining butter to the pan.

> If your honey has hardened, pop it in a bowl of hot water for 1 min.

Cook until thickened and sticky, ~{1-2%minutes}. Once thickened, gently turn the chicken thighs in the pan to coat in the glaze.

Share the glazed chicken thighs between your plates. Serve the zesty veg and herby chips alongside. Dollop some @mayonnaise{2%tbsp} onto your plates for dipping. Enjoy!